'''Willer Emilio Ditta Pérez''' (born 23 January 1998) is a Colombian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Liga MX]] club [[Cruz Azul]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]].

==Career==
Ditta began his football career at [[Barranquilla F.C.|Barranquilla]], where he emerged as a promising talent from the youth academy. He made his professional debut in 2018 before transferring to [[Atlético Junior]], where he achieved significant success by winning two [[Categoría Primera A|Primera A]] titles.

In January 2022, Ditta joined [[Newell's Old Boys]] on loan. Later that year, in November, Newell's exercised their purchase option to acquire him permanently, and he subsequently signed a three-year contract with the club.

On 6 July 2023, he joined [[Cruz Azul]]. In June 2025, he helped the club secure their seventh [[2025 CONCACAF Champions Cup|CONCACAF Champions Cup]] title with a dominant victory over the [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]].

